### H2 Structure (10 H2s — written as real user queries and long-tail keywords)

**H2 #1: What Are Old Money Nails, and Why Does Everyone Want Them Right Now?**
Define the aesthetic via heritage — not "anything classic counts." JFK Jr., Carolyn Bessette-Kennedy, New England estates, Park Avenue. The prep heritage angle, not the trend listicle angle. Primary keyword + user intent front-loaded. Mention almond nails as the ideal shape immediately.

**H2 #2: The One Nail Shape That Makes Every Old Money Design Actually Work**
Short to medium almond as the authenticated old money shape. Debunks the assumption that old money means long. Almond is softer than coffin, more refined than square, more heritage than stiletto. Natural link hook to: short-old-money-nails.

**H2 #3: What Exactly Makes a Nail Look Expensive Instead of Just Plain?**
Addresses the top pain point. Explains finish quality (always glossy, never matte), undertone matching (neutral-toned not warm), cuticle presentation, application cleanliness. The difference between "has old money polish" and "looks old money." This is the insight competitors completely miss.

**H2 #4: The Old Money Nail Colour Edit — From Sheer Pink to Deep Burgundy**
Core colour walk-through written as a curated wardrobe, not a listicle. Each shade explained by what it communicates, not just what it looks like. Sheer pink = effortless / deep red = confident power / milky white = inherited calm / navy = Ivy League / burgundy = evening heritage / espresso = modern classic. Link to: old-money-nail-colors for exact shade names and polish recommendations.

**H2 #5: The Old Money French Tip — Why This Specific Version Is the Signature Design**
French tip as heritage design — the micro tip, the soft base, the short almond shape. Explains why a chunky or bright-white thick tip is not old money. The viral TikTok "according to Pinterest this is called an old money French manicure" moment. Link to: old-money-french-tip-nails.

**H2 #6: Tortoiseshell, Marble, and the Subtle Design Details That Stay Within the Rules**
Addresses the pain point: "can I have ANY design or is it just plain colour?" Permission-giving with editorial rules. Tortoiseshell sunglasses → tortoiseshell nails. Marble → estate aesthetics. Pearl details → heritage jewellery. A single gold line at the tip. These are not maximalist — they are heritage-coded details.

**H2 #7: Old Money Nails vs Quiet Luxury Nails — Here Is the Actual Difference**
The most differentiated section on any ranking page. Old money = inherited heritage, prep culture, JFK Jr., New England, history. Quiet luxury = modern Succession-era restraint, contemporary stealth wealth, no historic reference. Both are understated — but the cultural root is entirely different. Bidirectional editorial link to: quiet-luxury-nails, framed as "read our quiet luxury guide to understand the distinction through both lenses."

**H2 #8: The Old Money Seasonal Palette — What Shifts and What Never Changes**
Seasonal flexibility without needing to read seasonal posts. The philosophy does not change — the palette does. Autumn/winter: espresso, burgundy, darker nudes, emerald. Spring/summer: sheer milky white, glazed pink, soft beige. The almond shape and glossy finish stay year-round. Natural link hooks to: old-money-nails-fall-winter and old-money-nails-spring-summer.

**H2 #9: How to Ask for Old Money Nails at the Salon (So You Actually Get What You Want)**
Practical execution — the gap between Pinterest saves and the finished set. Salon language: "short to medium almond," "sheer not opaque," "high-gloss topcoat, not matte," "micro French not traditional French." Bring a reference image. What questions to ask. What to avoid letting the tech default to.

**H2 #10: Is Old Money the Most Timeless Nail Aesthetic — or Will It Date Like Every Other Trend?**
Longevity framing. Nail experts (Thea Green/Nails.INC, Helen Marlen) on record: bare/naked manicures are a lasting movement driven by the old money aesthetic, not a trend cycle. 2026 nail trend data confirms: almond + sheer + glossy is the dominant shape/finish direction. Close with editorial outro. Link to: aesthetic-nail-ideas (the full universe) and rich-girl-nails (for readers wanting the technique-forward version of the expensive-looking mani).

